WEBVTT



00:00:17.664 --> 00:00:19.008
I told you

00:00:19.648 --> 00:00:21.248
I've told you twice

00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:23.296
I told you three times.

00:00:23.296 --> 00:00:24.384
What?

00:00:24.224 --> 00:00:25.984
What am I talking about?

00:00:26.368 --> 00:00:31.328
Well, it's the Gospel of Mark in chapter 16. You see,

00:00:31.200 --> 00:00:38.752
Mark chapter 16, well at the end of chapter 15 and all of chapter 16 has to do with the resurrection of the Lord.

00:00:38.784 --> 00:00:40.384
Of Jesus Christ.

00:00:41.152 --> 00:00:45.952
It's through the resurrection that Jesus defeated the final foe.

00:00:46.400 --> 00:00:47.712
Which is death.

00:00:48.608 --> 00:00:50.816
But he told the disciples

00:00:50.784 --> 00:00:52.736
This is what's going to happen.

00:00:53.216 --> 00:00:55.488
He told them various times.

00:00:56.032 --> 00:00:57.664
But like us,

00:00:57.760 --> 00:01:00.288
They questioned and they doubted.

00:01:01.504 --> 00:01:09.152
In John chapter 14 and verse 29, Jesus says to the disciples, "I'm going to tell you these things ahead of time."

00:01:09.024 --> 00:01:11.200
So that when they happen,

00:01:10.944 --> 00:01:12.512
You will believe it.

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:16.992
He tells them in John 16:4,

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:20.384
I'm going to tell you these things before they happen

00:01:20.352 --> 00:01:23.712
So that when they do happen, you will believe.

00:01:23.552 --> 00:01:25.120
What's he talking about?

00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:26.912
Resurrection

00:01:27.328 --> 00:01:33.536
It's almost like a mom or a dad that looks at their kids and says, "How many times do I have to tell you?"

00:01:33.312 --> 00:01:36.000
How many times do i have to repeat the same thing

00:01:37.152 --> 00:01:43.840
The book of Matthew records three different times that Jesus says to the disciples,

00:01:44.192 --> 00:01:47.872
It's Matthew 16:21.

00:01:48.096 --> 00:01:51.616
I'm going to be handed over to the Gentiles.

00:01:51.392 --> 00:01:59.328
They're going to persecute me. They're going to flog me. They're going to crucify me. But on the third day, I'm going to rise again.

00:01:59.328 --> 00:02:02.240
He says the same exact thing.

00:02:01.984 --> 00:02:05.440
In Matthew 17:22,

00:02:05.632 --> 00:02:08.992
And then in Matthew 20:17,

00:02:08.992 --> 00:02:11.008
Says the same thing

00:02:11.616 --> 00:02:16.000
How often, how many times does he have to say the same thing?

00:02:15.872 --> 00:02:17.088
To me

00:02:17.504 --> 00:02:21.920
How many times does he have to repeat the same thing to you?

00:02:22.464 --> 00:02:23.936
He's with you.

00:02:23.808 --> 00:02:26.816
He's never going to leave you. He loves you.

00:02:26.848 --> 00:02:30.784
He cares for you. He's compassionate for you.

00:02:31.168 --> 00:02:39.616
But we forget or we allow our circumstances to pressure us in such a way that we doubt that.

00:02:39.904 --> 00:02:41.792
Well, look with me in...

00:02:41.856 --> 00:02:46.624
Mark chapter 16 beginning in verse 1 when the Sabbath was over.

00:02:46.976 --> 00:02:49.696
Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother.

00:02:49.696 --> 00:02:55.360
James and Salome brought spices so that they might go to anoint Jesus' body.

00:02:56.128 --> 00:03:03.392
Very early the first day of the week just after sunrise they were on their way to the tomb and they asked each other

00:03:04.416 --> 00:03:06.656
Who's going to roll away the stone

00:03:06.528 --> 00:03:08.896
Away from the entrance of the tomb.

00:03:09.376 --> 00:03:12.000
But when they looked up they saw

00:03:11.808 --> 00:03:15.712
That the stone, which was very large, had been rolled away.

00:03:15.776 --> 00:03:24.480
As they entered the tomb, they saw a young man dressed in a white robe sitting on the right side and they were alarmed. Don't be alarmed.

00:03:24.576 --> 00:03:25.696
He said,

00:03:26.048 --> 00:03:28.224
you're looking for Jesus

00:03:28.384 --> 00:03:29.792
The Nazarene.

00:03:29.760 --> 00:03:31.520
Who was crucified

00:03:31.616 --> 00:03:33.376
He has risen.

00:03:33.472 --> 00:03:34.880
He's not here.

00:03:35.520 --> 00:03:36.896
He told you.

00:03:37.504 --> 00:03:39.712
He told you over and over again.

00:03:39.616 --> 00:03:41.312
It's going to happen.

00:03:42.400 --> 00:03:43.776
Check this out

00:03:44.256 --> 00:03:46.336
Whatever Jesus says,

00:03:46.720 --> 00:03:48.928
Is always trustworthy

00:03:49.152 --> 00:03:50.400
And true.

00:03:50.784 --> 00:03:51.872
Comma?

00:03:51.968 --> 00:03:53.344
Always.

00:03:53.664 --> 00:03:55.584
It's always trustworthy.

00:03:55.680 --> 00:03:59.744
It's always true. Whatever we find written in the scriptures,

00:03:59.648 --> 00:04:03.840
in which the Lord communicates to us, you can take it to the bank.

00:04:04.320 --> 00:04:12.320
No matter what it feels like, no matter what we think, no matter what we see, no matter what other people say to us, even if we say,

00:04:12.768 --> 00:04:18.368
Resurrection, it's never happened before. I don't see how it could happen.

00:04:18.848 --> 00:04:21.280
But Jesus said,

00:04:21.312 --> 00:04:23.072
Please don't forget.

00:04:23.872 --> 00:04:25.856
When Jesus speaks.

00:04:25.664 --> 00:04:28.192
His words are always trustworthy

00:04:28.352 --> 00:04:30.336
And it's always true.

00:04:30.528 --> 00:04:34.528
I want you to see in verse 7 something very important.

00:04:35.840 --> 00:04:41.248
The angel is talking to the believers, those that have gone to the tomb, and he says,

00:04:41.216 --> 00:04:44.288
Go and tell the disciples

00:04:44.736 --> 00:04:46.112
And Peter.

00:04:46.528 --> 00:04:49.632
Go and tell the disciples and Peter

00:04:49.952 --> 00:04:52.192
That he's going ahead of you into Galilee.

00:04:51.936 --> 00:04:59.104
Why would the angel be specific in naming Peter? Why? Because our brother had failed. He had blown it.

00:04:59.904 --> 00:05:02.016
It failed the Lord, remember?

00:05:02.432 --> 00:05:05.664
He fell short. He denied Jesus.

00:05:05.504 --> 00:05:07.040
Three times.

00:05:07.328 --> 00:05:12.160
Peter is the one that said, "Jesus, even if I have to die,

00:05:12.064 --> 00:05:14.400
I will never deny you.

00:05:15.648 --> 00:05:17.216
And when the time came,

00:05:17.728 --> 00:05:19.264
Our brother failed

00:05:19.936 --> 00:05:21.216
He failed.

00:05:21.632 --> 00:05:26.816
And it's the gospel of Luke where it says that when Jesus was taken into the praetorium,

00:05:26.656 --> 00:05:32.000
And he had been arrested that the eyes of Jesus and the eyes of Peter met

00:05:32.224 --> 00:05:36.512
And Peter was broken after he had denied the Lord.

00:05:36.736 --> 00:05:38.016
And he wept.

00:05:37.760 --> 00:05:39.168
bitterly.

00:05:40.320 --> 00:05:42.112
You ever failed the Lord?

00:05:42.016 --> 00:05:43.520
I know that I have.

00:05:44.448 --> 00:05:49.920
Can I remind you that there are several people in the scriptures that failed God?

00:05:50.336 --> 00:05:53.824
The Samaritan woman from John chapter 4

00:05:53.632 --> 00:05:56.320
She had relational issues.

00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:58.048
Abraham

00:05:57.984 --> 00:05:59.488
He lied.

00:05:59.232 --> 00:06:00.960
The father of faith.

00:06:00.896 --> 00:06:04.224
You had a problem with with lying noah

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:05.568
Noah.

00:06:05.376 --> 00:06:06.848
Got drunk.

00:06:07.104 --> 00:06:11.296
David, what can we say about King David and Bathsheba?

00:06:11.264 --> 00:06:13.280
Committed adultery.

00:06:13.344 --> 00:06:16.352
Jonah, what can we say about Jonah?

00:06:16.320 --> 00:06:18.400
Jonah fled from God.

00:06:18.496 --> 00:06:19.808
Elijah.

00:06:20.768 --> 00:06:24.224
Elijah had emotional problems.

00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:26.624
Jacob, Jacob!

00:06:26.656 --> 00:06:28.864
You wouldn't want to.

00:06:28.608 --> 00:06:32.512
He would not want to enter into a business dealing with Jacob.

00:06:32.864 --> 00:06:34.368
The disciples

00:06:34.848 --> 00:06:37.120
When they should have been awake.

00:06:36.928 --> 00:06:40.384
During the times of Jesus most difficult time

00:06:40.672 --> 00:06:42.304
They fell asleep.

00:06:43.296 --> 00:06:46.528
But here's something that I wrote. Our failure.

00:06:46.464 --> 00:06:49.984
He does not stop Jesus from reaching heaven.

00:06:49.728 --> 00:06:50.656
Out.

00:06:50.464 --> 00:06:51.552
To us.

00:06:51.360 --> 00:06:55.168
Would you please remember that, my dear Christian family?

00:06:55.840 --> 00:06:59.360
We're gonna make a mistake we're gonna fall short

00:06:59.328 --> 00:07:03.072
All of us have sinned and we all fall short of the glory of God.

00:07:02.752 --> 00:07:06.688
But that does not stop our Savior from reaching out to us.

00:07:07.040 --> 00:07:10.880
I want you to look at verse 15 with me.

00:07:10.624 --> 00:07:12.512
Mark 16:

00:07:13.664 --> 00:07:17.376
It says in verse 15, "The Jesus said to them,

00:07:17.600 --> 00:07:21.312
Go into all the world

00:07:21.152 --> 00:07:23.488
And preach the gospel

00:07:23.520 --> 00:07:25.888
To all creation.

00:07:25.728 --> 00:07:28.320
I want you to notice that first of all

00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:32.800
The instruction to go into all the world

00:07:32.736 --> 00:07:34.560
For us as Christians,

00:07:34.592 --> 00:07:36.288
It's not a suggestion.

00:07:36.704 --> 00:07:38.336
It's a command.

00:07:38.752 --> 00:07:48.800
Now, I know that it sounds pretty lofty going to all the world. I mean, come on, I'm only one person. How am I going to go? How is it possible for me to go into all

00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:51.488
To all the world, can I make a suggestion for you?

00:07:52.032 --> 00:07:53.952
What if we look at it this way?

00:07:54.912 --> 00:07:58.816
I may not be able to go into all the world

00:07:59.520 --> 00:08:02.048
But I can't go into my world

00:08:02.656 --> 00:08:04.928
The people with whom I live.

00:08:05.248 --> 00:08:07.552
The people with whom I work.

00:08:07.648 --> 00:08:09.632
The people with whom

00:08:09.472 --> 00:08:12.768
I spend recreational time with.

00:08:13.056 --> 00:08:14.368
The people...

00:08:14.112 --> 00:08:17.056
that I live next door to. That's my world.

00:08:17.568 --> 00:08:20.192
Go into your world

00:08:20.960 --> 00:08:22.528
It's not a suggestion.

00:08:22.528 --> 00:08:28.768
If you've been touched by the love of Jesus Christ, we ought to be excited about sharing that.

00:08:28.640 --> 00:08:30.080
With somebody.

00:08:30.624 --> 00:08:33.984
But the opportunity to go across the sea

00:08:34.080 --> 00:08:37.152
To go into all the world exists for all of us.

00:08:37.408 --> 00:08:39.360
We have the opportunity.

00:08:39.552 --> 00:08:41.824
The question is, is it a priority?

00:08:41.728 --> 00:08:44.768
To go across the sea

00:08:44.864 --> 00:08:47.168
You just need to see

00:08:47.200 --> 00:08:48.352
the cross.

00:08:48.512 --> 00:08:49.952
Let me repeat that.

00:08:50.560 --> 00:08:53.504
To go across the scene

00:08:53.696 --> 00:08:56.416
You just need to see it.

00:08:56.192 --> 00:08:57.408
The cross.

00:08:57.632 --> 00:09:00.384
Take note of what Jesus has done for you.

00:09:00.480 --> 00:09:05.344
And you will find that passion, that love and motivation.

00:09:06.464 --> 00:09:08.704
To go into all the world.

00:09:09.024 --> 00:09:13.792
The resurrection of Jesus offers eternal implications for you.

00:09:13.536 --> 00:09:14.592
For me.

00:09:14.688 --> 00:09:17.408
Let me leave you with that verse with this verse

00:09:17.952 --> 00:09:22.368
The book of Romans chapter 8 verse 11 the Apostle Paul says

00:09:22.272 --> 00:09:24.704
If the spirit of him

00:09:25.216 --> 00:09:27.808
who raised Jesus from the dead.

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:29.664
Living you.

00:09:30.080 --> 00:09:31.648
Then the one...

00:09:31.392 --> 00:09:34.560
that raised Jesus from the dead?

00:09:34.624 --> 00:09:36.352
will give life

00:09:36.192 --> 00:09:38.016
To your mortal body

00:09:38.176 --> 00:09:39.552
Through his spirit.

00:09:39.328 --> 00:09:40.896
You know what Paul is saying?

00:09:41.344 --> 00:09:42.720
Eternal life.

00:09:43.456 --> 00:09:47.552
Because of the resurrection of Jesus Christ my brother and sister

00:09:47.712 --> 00:09:50.080
We have the hope of eternal life.

00:09:50.560 --> 00:09:53.600
We're living in this world.

00:09:53.344 --> 00:09:56.192
But this is not our final resting place

00:09:56.256 --> 00:09:58.144
We're only passing through.

00:09:58.784 --> 00:10:01.248
We have the hope of eternal life.

00:10:01.664 --> 00:10:07.776
Paul says in the book of 2 Corinthians chapter 5 that when this tent is destroyed,

00:10:07.776 --> 00:10:09.472
We have a house.

00:10:09.408 --> 00:10:11.776
That's not built by human hands.

00:10:12.160 --> 00:10:15.808
but it's built by the Spirit of God that's waiting for us.

00:10:16.096 --> 00:10:17.600
Let me pray for us.

00:10:19.360 --> 00:10:23.520
Our Father, as we talk about the resurrection of our Savior,

00:10:24.192 --> 00:10:26.752
Lord, what a glorious miracle!

00:10:27.168 --> 00:10:32.288
Lord, I pray that it would not just be a religious tradition that Easter

00:10:32.192 --> 00:10:38.656
The bunny and the colored eggs, but God, that it would be something that is so real to us.

00:10:39.168 --> 00:10:41.952
That Jesus, your son,

00:10:42.496 --> 00:10:45.312
Was crucified, was buried,

00:10:45.248 --> 00:10:47.936
And he defeated death.

00:10:47.968 --> 00:10:50.880
And now it offers salvation freely

00:10:50.816 --> 00:10:53.056
To all who would receive.

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:54.784
And we pray.

00:10:54.752 --> 00:10:56.608
In Jesus name

00:10:57.280 --> 00:10:58.400
Amen.
